blocks.text: Into New Hampshire and a decision to take the motor road to the top of Mt. Washington, highest point in New England at 6,288 feet. Toll is $5 for car and driver, plus $1 for each passenger.

The road to the top of the hill is a steady climb of eight miles, half of which was built more than 100 years ago. The views are spectacular actually. A considerable part gravel, narrow and not overly well protected at the edges.
The very top...here in 1934 the wind velocity was 231 miles, highest ever recorded. Climbers with packs on their backs are everywhere.

Bill pretends to fill his hat with water from old wood pump along street.
End - trip to Delaware.
